        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Isolate Claude OAuth usage from CLI refresh",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- prevent Claude OAuth usage fetches from delegating token refresh through the local Claude CLI\n- skip CLI version detection for Claude OAuth usage results so Waybar polling does not spawn CLI/MCP side effects\n- cover the OAuth delegated-refresh gate on both macOS test targets and Linux-safe tests\n\n## Root Cause\n\nWaybar invokes the CodexBar CLI repeatedly for Claude OAuth usage. That path could still fall through to Claude CLI-backed delegated refresh and CLI version detection, which can spawn local MCP server launchers. On the affected Linux setup those Bun-backed MCP launches were aborting repeatedly, creating a Waybar/coredump loop.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter PlatformGatingTests`\n- `swift test --filter ClaudeOAuthDelegatedRefreshLinuxTests`\n- `swift test`\n- `swift build`\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh lint-linux`\n- `swift build -c release`\n- Waybar script smoke check using the rebuilt CLI: exited 0, no stderr, Bun/MCP launcher process count stayed flat\n",
